description: The conflict escalates.
name: Too Far Gone, Pt. 4

description: This is it! The penultimate issue of PROJECT SUPERPOWERS! Witness the terrible resurrection of the Claw and the ultimate fate of Zeus as our reborn heroes struggle with the challenges of their very existence and place in this strange new world!

The Lovecraft-inspired event of the year continues! Darkness is rising and soon all will hear the Calling! Clayton Diggs teeters on the brink of madness as he struggles to identify the first piece in this bizarre, paralyzing puzzle - all before a great one awakes and the world changes forever! An all-new ongoing supernatural horror series with a decidedly modern spin. Cover by Federico Piatti.

Cassie has found a friend for the first time in her life! But there's more to Sarah than meets the eye. What is the secret behind the arcade game BLUD BUS? And what does it have to do with the kids who keep turning up dead in a cornfield? The story behind Cassie's first case gets twisted!

List of covers and their creators:

CoverNameCreator(s)Sidebar Location
RegRegular CoverTim Seeley & Carlos Badilla1
VarVariant CoverMike Norton & Nei Ruffino2

TWISTORY STUDIOS presents PAOLO PARENTE'S pin-up girl & war machine universe like you have never seen. Issue #3 is the thrilling conclusion to the covert Allied mission to loot a castle deep behind enemy lines, and they inadvertently save the world from destruction. Meanwhile Soviet Commander Koshka Rudinova and her well-armored KV-47 robot team is on the run after discovery an Axis air patrol. Be sure not to miss the final of latest three-issue series from PAOLO PARENTE's ever-growing DUST universe. This time, it's DUST WARS!
name: Gunter Valley: Part Three

description: Daken barely survived his encounter with Frank Castle, but that only makes him more dangerous than ever -- especially when Wolverine shows up to save the day. Killing two birds with one stone has never been more appealing...
name: Punishment, Part 3

description: THE HULK HAS RETURNED. And three years of epic storytelling explodes as GREK PAK and PAUL PELLETIER bring you the biggest conclusion imaginable--SKAAR, SON OF HULK, finally confronts the father who abandoned him at birth in pain and fire. It's the heartrending, senses-shattering climax to WORLD WAR HULKS--and the Incredible Hulks will never be the same!
name: Sons of Wrath; Act 3: Slave to Memory

description: Gen 13 finds an unspoiled, secret oasis in the blasted ruins of America and will do anything to protect it. But a dark secret lies at the heart of this paradise - a secret that may claim the life of Burnout!
name: Pocatello, Part Three: We're the Good Guys

description: As Yura continues her foray into the glamorous world of acting, she's starting to learn that success is often marred with setbacks and compromises. Although she fails to land the lead role in a new drama penned by famous screenwriter Maki Todo, she does succeed in getting offered the part of the heroine's friend. However, her boss Keiichi cautions Yura that her increasing popularity will result in greater scrutiny of her private life by the paparazzi. Can Yura continue growing as an actress while keeping her budding relationships with Q-ta and Haruka in check?
name: Vol. 4

description: From the pages of GREEN HORNET: YEAR ONE comes the solo adventures of KATO! Kato is on his own as he tracks down a murderer and finds himself caught among the intrigue and danger of wartime America and the Japanese and Nazi are on the mainland! Now, in addition to the murderer he's trailing, Kato is onto bigger game - spies and saboteurs!
name: Way of the Ninja, Part Three

description: As Yura's friends gather to celebrate the premiere of the first episode of her TV show, she's nowhere to be seen. Having taken up Q-ta's offer of a hot springs vacation, Yura finds herself alone with him in a luxurious hotel room. Is she prepared to go all the way with Q-ta, or will her manager Mizurogi spoil the fun once again...?
name: Vol. 5

description: Stranded in the Pennsylvania woods, the final three hippies are in a fight for their lives against an army of zombies made up of their former friends and lovers. To make matters worse, the zombies appear to be controlled by a messianic zombie named Deadhead. Even as the few survivors struggle to survive the night, it remains unclear if they will be able to escape the zombie virus.

volume.name: Escape of the Living Dead: Airborne

description: Sara Pezzini can gain an important ally in Abby van Alstine, the Necromancer, but only if Sara can keep her alive! Abby's visit to New York City is interrupted by a demonic attack, and her only chance for survival is entering the world of the Witchblade.
name: The Demon Within

description: Following the global havoc created by the frog war, and with the B.P.R.D. now operating under strict U.N. oversight, our heroes face new horrors. People are once again vanishing from small towns, monsters are roaming in the woods, and a strange new creature arrives to create hell on earth.
name: 1 of 5

first_appearance_teams.name: Bureau for Paranormal Research and Defense

team_credits.name: Bureau for Paranormal Research and Defense

volume.name: B.P.R.D.: Hell on Earth - New World

description: But now there are rumors in the capital of another mysterious and powerful girl who also claims to be the Priestess of the Dragon God! Akane and the Eight Guardians go to investigate the impostor, but are completely unprepared for what they find...
name: Vol. 3

description: As Akane lays plans to find the remaining two of her Eight Guardians, she stumbles onto a mysterious instrument that sends her into a deep, paralyzing sleep. Unfortunately, the only one who can save her is one of the two Guardians she hasn't yet met!
name: Vol. 4

description: The monk-prince Eisen has become the seventh of the Eight Guardians, but one last Guardian remains shrouded in mystery. As the search goes on for Akane's final protector, Akane still struggles to accept the power inside her...and then, Major General Tachibana goes missing!
name: Vol. 5

description: Tomomasa is missing, and Akane and the Guardians must hunt high and low to find him. Their search brings them to a magical tree that reveals a harrowing vision of Tomomasa being led from the capital. Can Akane and the others find him before he is lost forever?
name: Vol. 6

description: Recently the capital city has been overrun by a horde of vengeful spirits. With the power of the Dragon God at her command, it's up to Akane to protect her friends from the mounting danger. If only her friends could get along with each other!
name: Vol. 7

description: Princess Fuji informs Akane that the Eight Guardians must find the Four Sacred Talismans if they ever hope to control the Four Gods. That's going to be difficult since the location of these sacred objects is secret. Akane's got to be quick, however--Shirin and Sefle are looking for them too.
name: Vol. 8

description: Shirin will do anything to get her hands on the Four Sacred Talismans. Disguised as Akane, she tries flirting with Eisen. When that fails, she travels to the Matsuo Taisha Shrine and tries to kill Takamichi!
name: Vol. 9

description:
Cover: Clint Langley (Sinister Dexter)

  • Droid Life (Cat Sullivan)
  • Judge Dredd - The Connoisseur (part 3 - final part) (Gordon Rennie - Karl Richardson)
  • The Red Seas - Hell and High Water (part 10) (Ian Edginton - Steve Yeowell)
  • Sinister Dexter - The Why-Shaped Cut (part 5) (Dan Abnett - Anthony Williams/Rob Taylor)
  • Savage - Book Six - Crims (part 13) (Pat Mills - Patrick Goddard)
  • Strontium Dog - The Life and Death of Johnny Alpha (part 9) (John Wagner - Carlos and Hector Ezquerra)
name: Prog 1697

description: This second in a series of five one-shot stories concerns the enigmatic Wilson, the self-professed protector of Chinatown and confidant to Matty Roth. Wilson's always said he'd "own" the DMZ in the end, and now, with the U.S. poised to steamroll its way into the city, it's do-or-die time for the old man. Artist Nathan Fox (Pigeons from Hell) returns to DMZ for another gorgeous, detail-rich issue.
name: Collective Punishment: Ghost Protector

description: Trying to survive in rigid 9th century Norway, young outcasts Erik and Ingrid continue fleeing all forms of society, turning increasingly to the past, to paganism and the "old ways," hoping to find something – anything – they can feel is their own. But they're dogged every step of the way. The Church sends out heavily armed search and rescue teams to bring Ingrid back to the flock from which she recently ran away.
name: Metal: The Greening

description: Southeast Asia. Blue skies...green palms...tropical heat...and lurking death. As our heroes pass through Singapore and Myanmar, they are attacked by the deadliest Stands yet, Ebony Devil and Yellow Temperance. Then, in India, Polnareff meets the man who killed his sister. But can he avenge her death...or will he join her in the grave?
name: The Emperor and the Hanged Man

description: Avdol has a bullet in his brain, and the heroes face a seemingly unbeatable pair of enemies--the Emperor, whose spirit takes the form of a gun, and the Hanged Man, which dwells in mirrors! With death coming closer in every piece of glass, do Polnareff and Kakyoin have a chance?
name: Terror in India

description: Straight out of the JUSTICE LEAGUE: THE RISE OF ARSENAL miniseries, Arsenal signs up with Deathstroke and Cheshire when the Titans target a child slavery ring for takedown. What they unearth will shock you to the core!
name: Suffer the Children

description: Pursued by the deadly treads of "Wheel of Fortune," the heroes cross from India to Pakistan, where they spend the night in an ancient, fog-shrouded town. But little do they know that they have walked into the hands of their enemy...the twin right hands of Enyaba Geil, who wants bloody revenge on the men who killed her son! Invaded by Enyaba's stand "Justice," the heroes' own bodies turn against them, while an army of zombies slouches closer. Will they escape...or will they be dead by dawn?
name: City of Death

description: To eliminate the "Lovers" Stand within Joseph Joestar's body, Polnareff and Kakyoin shrink their Stands to microscopic size, for a fantastic voyage into Joseph Joestar's brain tissue! Then, the heroes cross the Arabian desert on camelback, braving searing heat by day and deadly dreams by night...
name: The Arabian Nightmare

description: After a nightmarish journey through the desert, the heroes find themselves on the western shore of Saudi Arabia, only a short distance from Egypt. Separated from his friends, Polnareff finds a lamp and unleashes a genie that offers to grant him his dearest wishes! Does the world contain stranger things than Stands? Then, the heroes enter a submarine for the last leg of their journey. But beneath the waters of the Red Sea, they find themselves trapped with a terrifying stowaway...
name: The Three Wishes

description: At last, Jotaro and his companions have made it to Egypt! Now only a journey down the Nile stands between them and their adversary...that, and nine new Stand users, the Great Gods of Egypt, who serve Dio with blind fanaticism. Gruesome death waits beneath the desert sands, and to stand a chance, the heroes must tame a new ally, a vicious brute whose Tarot Card is "The Fool"!
name: Iggy the Fool and the Great God Geb

description: A long journey down the Nile separates the heroes from their destination...and danger awaits every step of the way. In Kom Ombo, Polnareff fights a mighty swordsman imbued with the power of Anubis, the Egyptian God of the Dead! Then, in the Valley of the Kings, Joseph Joestar meets a mysterious woman...and finds his powers of attraction increased to the point of mortal danger...
name: The Deadly Sword

description: Quelle horreur! Mariah, the master of magnetism, has Joseph Joestar in her grip...lovingly caressed by the ever-growing weight of 10 tons of steel! As Joseph is slowly crushed to death by every iron object for miles around, Polnareff must face Alessi, whose Egyptian God Stand turns the French fighter into a shadow of his former self...
name: The Shadow of Set

description: "Would you like to play a game?" In a café in the shadow of the pyramids, a sharp-dressed man challenges the heroes to a game of chance. But what starts as a simple bet turns into their deadliest challenge so far...
name: D'Arby the Gambler

description: The magic book of Mondatta has shown the future: Jotaro with a bullet through his head!  Can he escape his fate?! As the heroes race against time to find Dio's secret lair, Iggi, the dog, is the first to discover the location. But Dio's guardian, a hawk with the power of an Egyptian god, will kill anything…and anyone...who threatens his master. It's the ultimate superpowered dog vs. bird battle!
name: The Claws of Horus

description: Trapped within an extradimensional space, Jotaro, Joseph and Kakyoin must fight a deadly new opponent, Terrence T. D'Arby, brother of the poker player Daniel D'Arby! Though his brother was the most fearsome gambler on earth, Terence never once lost a game to him...for reasons which our heroes are about to discover. His Stand is deadly, his instincts are unbeatable, and his weapon of choice is video games. Will the clicking of the 16-bit cartridge be the last thing they hear?
name: D'Arby the Player

description: Within the mazelike interior of Dio's mansion in Cairo, the heroes search for the lair of the vampire. But Dio has saved his deadliest henchman for last. Now Polnareff, Avdol and Iggy the dog must fight against the most brutal enemy they have ever encountered…
name: Showdown

description: Kakyoin, Polnareff and Joseph, who have pursued Dio from Japan to Egypt, find themselves hunted as night falls and Dio reveals his true power. But is Dio's Stand, "The World," already too powerful to be stopped?
name: Dio's World

description: Headquarters in Kyoto learns that the rogue behavior of their branch troop captain in Osaka is stirring up resentment among the local populace. Kondo takes Okita, Sei and the first troop to Osaka to investigate. They find that Tani Sanjuro, the captain of the seventh troop, is a hard-hearted man who rules with an iron fist. Will Kondo find a way to deal with this ogre, or will he need to take extreme measures to eliminate him?
name: Vol. 17

description: Japan is approaching a tipping point, with increasing pressure from the West to open its borders. The Shinsengumi are being trained to use firearms, but Okita refuses, insisting on the way of the sword. He represents many in the group who cling to old samurai values. But it is clear that the times are changing and the Shinsengumi embodies the "old guard." Will they survive the coming upheavals?
name: Vol. 18

description: Gail Simone’s beloved series continues! Following an attack on the police escort returning Mayor Fury to Tranquility, Sheriff Lindo and Deputy Duray find themselves in a deadly predicament! And Fury is in the fight of his life against this mysterious new villain. Will help from the town arrive in time – or will the man who crushed the Nazi war machine finally be defeated?
name: Homecoming-Part Two: Of Cabbages and Kings

volume.name: Welcome to Tranquility: One Foot in the Grave

description: There's no other way to say it: In this issue ... Spider-Man 's entire life is completely destroyed. Read the series that has fans and critics hooked as Brian Michael Bendis and David Lafuente rock out another unbelievable issue!
name: Tainted Love: Part 5 of 6

description: He's back! Straight from the Child's Play movies, and slashing a bloody swath through comics! Chucky is here! When Chucky sets his sight on a grown up Andy Barclay, the first person to ever encounter the murderous doll, you know that the blood is going to flow! Intense horror in this all-new limited series!

"Does the world need another vampire?"  This is the question Josesph Michael Linsner asks and answers in an early preview where he shares some early sketches and thoughts on the character development of Ivory.

The amazing World War Hulk saga continues.

Doctor Strange claims the power of the demonic Zom - but has he just become a bigger threat than the Hulk?!

Mr Fantastic, Iron Man, Black Bolt and the Avengers face a terrifying punishment - can boy genius Amadeus Cho stop the Hulk's rampage?

By Greg Pak, John Romita Jr and Carlo Pagulayan.
name: World War Hulk part four

description:
Gin's Top 5 List of Things to Look For When Hiring a Maid

  1. Alien robot head? Attached!
  2. King-sized pooper scooper? Check!
  3. Mad scientist to keep mechanical maid army running? Check!
  4. Main battle tank gassed up? Check!
  5. Extra-manly moustache? Check! What?!

Chapter Titles

  • Lesson 140. "Please Cooperate in Separating the Trash"
  • Lesson 141. "There Are No Save Points in Real Life"
  • Lesson 142. "Nothing Can Compete With a Woman's Tears"
  • Lesson 143. "Too Much Cute Is Creepy"
  • Lesson 144. "Western Songs Are Hard To Learn"
  • Lesson 145. "People Who Say They Are Doing it For the Sake of Another Are Mostly Doing it for Themselves"
  • Lesson 146. "Some Data Cannot be Deleted"
  • Lesson 147. "Only One Hour of Video Games per Day"
  • Lesson 148. "Don't Spent Your Whole Day Off Playing Video Games"
name: Vol. 17

description:
Hasegawa's Top 5 Reasons for Hating Valentine's Day

  1. Giant robot space women can't appreciate your earthling sensibilities.
  2. You may think your sweet wrestling moves are cool, but women just think you're perverted.
  3. Sometimes you wish girls would just fall out of the sky, but it sucks if they land on you!
  4. Sure, some call it peeping, but I call it "admiring from a distance (through a telescope)."
  5. If you give her chocolate, she'll just get fat (and then fall out of the sky on you).

Chapter Titles

  • Lesson 149. "Life and Video Games Are Full of Bugs"
  • Lesson 150. "Disasters Come in Threes"
  • Lesson 151. "Even Heroes Have Problems"
  • Lesson 152. "Try to See People's Good Points Instead of the Bad"
  • Lesson 153. "When You're on a Train, Hold On to the Straps with Both Hands"
  • Lesson 154. "Men, Be Dorks"
  • Lesson 155. "Love Conquers All"
  • Lesson 156. "If You Want to Lose Weight, Move"
  • Lesson 157. "If You Want to Lose Weight, Don't Eat"
name: Vol. 18

description:
Top Five Things to Consider Before Joining the Shinsengumi

  1. Your sword might be cursed by the vengeful spirit of an anime otaku.
  2. Rivalries and betrayals may lead to a short and painful career.
  3. No Shonen Jump manga allowed!
  4. You're a nobody unless you can afford the sword with the built-in MP3 player.
  5. The black uniforms are killer on a hot summer day!

Chapter Titles

  • Lesson 158. "Most New Things Have Too Many Functions"
  • Lesson 159. "Rules Are Meant to Be Broken"
  • Lesson 160. "Otaku Are Very Talkative"
  • Lesson 161. "True Fanatics Need Three Each"
  • Lesson 162. "There's a Fine Line Between One's Good Points and Bad Points"
  • Lesson 163. "A Uniform Makes You Look 20 Percent Better"
  • Lesson 164. "Don't Play on the Railroad Tracks"
  • Lesson 165. "A Schemer Gets Caught in His Own Scheme"
  • Lesson 166. "Important Things Are Hard to See"
name: Vol. 19

description: Asuka's protégé Yamato has fallen in love with a girl and needs help winning her over. He pleads with Asuka to go on a practice date with him--and play the role of the girl! Practice makes perfect, but will that be the case for Yamato?
name: Vol. 6

description: Asuka's friend Juta needs to keep his identity as renowned shojo author Jewel Sachihana a secret, so why is he agreeing to do an autograph session?! The answer may lie in a letter from a certain fan...
name: Vol. 7

description: Before the Straw Hats can get the Merry Go fixed, they must face the Foxy Pirates in a game called a Davy Back Fight. Will the Straw Hats find a way to win the three challenges, or will they lose their crew? And what's in store when Admiral Aokiji, who knows of Nico Robin's mysterious past, finds them?
name: The City of Water, Water Seven
El Misterio de los Astronautas - 3er. Capítulo
Los Misterios de la Muralla China - 32o. Capítulo
